        <div type="translation" resp="part:dogo">
 	<p n="1">... this (ayam) great sacrifice (mahākratuḥ) took place (abhūt) using eighty (aśītyā) ....</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This fragment of a schist inscription was reused in a conduit for libations (a so-called <foreign>somasūtra</foreign>) in the brick temple Preah Ko that must have been erected not more than one or two centuries after the inscription was engarved.</p>
         <!-- dogo: Epic is full of rājasūyas and horse-sacrfices that are described as mahākratu.  Eighty officiants, or eighty sacrificial victims, would make a pretty big sacrifice.  Perhaps you thought of all this but decided that actually advancing an interpretation would be too bold. -->
         </div>
